  <section>
    <div class="section-label">10</div>
    <h2>Landscape Fit</h2>
    <p>Terrestrial silicon remains viable short-term but encounters hard limits at orbital scale: radiation flux, launch mass constraints, and the absence of convective cooling. This framework converges three maturing streams—orbital solar (ARAQYS, 2025), ISRU chemistry (NASA), and diamond electronics (GaN-on-diamond, Diamond Quanta 2025)—none of which individually solves the substrate problem.</p>
